tempo /ˈtɛmpəʊ/

(tempos) 

1. N-SING The tempo of an event is the speed at which it happens. (事件发展的) 速度 

例： ...owing to the slow tempo of change in an overwhelmingly rural country. …由于一个高度农业化国家变革的缓慢速度。 

2. N-VAR The tempo of a piece of music is the speed at which it is played. (音乐的) 节奏 

例： In a new recording, the Boston Philharmonic tried the original tempo. 在一张新唱片中，波士顿爱乐乐团尝试了音乐原本的节奏。

